sections.History:
===Season 1===
The singer [[Marillion]] offers to sing [[Tyrion Lannister]] a song about his father's victory at King's Landing, the thought of which turns Tyrion's stomach.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

[[File:Slaughter.png|thumb|left|Ser Gregor Clegane kills Rhaegar Targaryen's family]][[Catelyn Stark]] talks to her son [[Robb Stark|Robb]] about the Sack of King's Landing. She mentions that Tywin Lannister slew the young Targaryen children, referring to the murders of Prince Aegon and Princess Rhaenys, and how he has not gotten any more merciful with age.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Pointy End]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

At [[Castle Black]], [[Aemon]], revealing himself to be the uncle of the Mad King, tells [[Jon Snow]] how he heard of the ruin of his house. He becomes angry when talking about the slaughter of the children.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Baelor]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===Season 3===

[[Thoros]] of Myr recalls how, following the sack of the city, the bodies of Prince [[Aegon Targaryen (Son of Rhaegar)|Aegon]] and Princess [[Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Rhaegar)|Rhaenys]] were presented by Ser [[Gregor Clegane]] before the [[Iron Throne]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Walk of Punishment]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
[[File:Kingslayer.png|thumb|left|Jaime Lannister slays the Mad King]]
Jaime reveals to [[Brienne]] that, when his father marched to the gates of [[King's Landing]], both Jaime and [[Varys]] advised Aerys not to trust Lord Tywin. Aerys, however, followed [[Grand Maester]] [[Pycelle]]'s counsel and had the city gates opened, allowing the Lannister forces to sack the city. Jaime advised Aerys to surrender, only for the Mad King to demand Jaime bring his father's head and order Lord [[Rossart]] to ignite the caches of [[wildfire]] hidden throughout the city to burn it to the ground with all its inhabitants. Jaime killed [[Rossart]] and then Aerys, who kept muttering &quot;burn them all&quot; as he died. Aerys seemingly believed the massive wildfire inferno would also transmute him into a [[dragon]]. Afterward, [[Eddard Stark]] reached the [[Great Hall (Red Keep)|throne room]] and found Jaime along with the two corpses.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Kissed by Fire]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
